               <p>- Gearey. I am the wife of the last witness. I saw the prisoner confused, and perceived a pot behind him; in my fright I put my hands to his pocket, and found two pewter pots, one in each coat pocket; one our's the other Mrs. Trinder's.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>She took them up through the flap of my coat; it lay over them; they were not in my pocket.</p>
               <p>Prosecutrix. He was standing up when I took them out of his pocket.</p>
